> Hey Michel
>
> One thing to keep in mind when you are considering price, especially with
> things like bearings and probably wheel cylinders, is who manufactured
them.
> I've order bearing from California Imports in B.C. and it looked like a
> great price - until I got the bearings.  They were all made in China.  If
> you order from Ronnie you at least have a choice as to whether you want to
> use cheap bearings or not as he stocks bearings from different
> manufacturers.
>
> I've ordered stuff from www.johnsbugshop.com out of Niagara Falls and all
of
> the bearings were either Fag or SKF - I betcha 5 bucks if I had ordered
> those bearings from California Imports they would have been made in China
> crappola.
>
> jdd 60 std
